basisset.dc:title: aug-cc-pVTZ-J
basisset.dc:description: The aug-cc-pVTZ-J basis sets developed by Sauer and co-workers are modifications of the aug-cc-pVTZ basis sets by Dunning and co-workers (T. H. Dunning, Jr. J. Chem. Phys. 90, 1007 (1989); R. A. Kendall, T. H. Dunning, Jr. and R. J. Harrison, J. Chem. Phys. 96, 6769 (1992); D. E. Woon and T. H. Dunning, Jr. J. Chem. Phys. J. Chem. Phys. 98, 1358 (1993)). They were optimized for the calculation of NMR indirect nuclear spin-spin coupling constants with either correlated wavefunction methods such as SOPPA and SOPPA(CCSD) or density functional theory methods. Currently the basis sets exist for: H, B, C, N, O, F, Al, P, Si, S, Cl, Se The composition of the basis sets are: for H: (10s3p1d) contracted to [6s3p1d] for B, C, N, O, F: (15s6p3d1f) contracted to [9s5p3d1f] for Al, P, Si, S, Cl: (20s10p6d1f) contracted to [10s7p6d1f] for Se: (23s14p10d2f) contracted to [12s9p6d2f] The references for the basis sets are: T. Enevoldsen, J. Oddershede and S. P. A. Sauer, Theor. Chem. Acc. 100, 275-284 (1998) P. F. Provasi, G. A. Aucar and S. P. A. Sauer, J. Chem. Phys. 115, 1324 (2001) P. F. Provasi and S. P. A. Sauer, J. Chem. Theory Comput. (submitted) Y. Yu. Rusakov, L. B. Krivdin, S. P. A. Sauer, E. P. Levanova and G. G. Levkovskaya, Magn. Res. Chem. (submitted) The performance of the basis sets in correlated wavefunction calculations was investigated e.g. in: T. Enevoldsen, J. Oddershede and S. P. A. Sauer, Theor. Chem. Acc. 100, 275-284 (1998) P. F. Provasi, G. A. Aucar and S. P. A. Sauer, J. Chem. Phys. 115, 1324 (2001) L. B. Krivdin, S. P. A. Sauer, J. E. Peralta and R. H. Contreras, Magn. Res. Chem. 40, 187-194 (2002) The performance of the basis sets in DFT/B3LYP calculations was investigated e.g. in: L. B. Krivdin, S. P. A. Sauer, J. E. Peralta and R. H. Contreras, Magn. Res. Chem. 40, 187-194 (2002) J. E. Peralta, G. E. Scuseria, J. R. Cheeseman and M. J. Frisch, Chem. Phys. Lett. 375, 452-458 (2003). The aug-cc-pVTZ-J basis sets developed by Sauer and co-workers are modifications of the aug-cc-pVTZ basis sets by Dunning and co-workers (T. H. Dunning, Jr. J. Chem. Phys. 90, 1007 (1989); R. A. Kendall, T. H. Dunning, Jr. and R. J. Harrison, J. Chem. Phys. 96, 6769 (1992); D. E. Woon and T. H. Dunning, Jr. J. Chem. Phys. 98, 1358 (1993) N. B. Balabanov, K. A. Peterson, J. Chem. Phys. 123, 64107 (2005)). They were optimized for the calculation of NMR indirect nuclear spin-spin coupling constants or ESR hyperfine coupling constants with either correlated wavefunction methods such as SOPPA and SOPPA(CCSD) or density functional theory methods. Currently the basis sets exist for: H, B, C, N, O, F, Al, P, Si, S, Cl, Se, Sc, Ti, V, Cr, Mn, Fe, Co, Ni, Cu, Zn The composition of the basis sets are: for H: (10s3p1d) contracted to [6s3p1d] for B, C, N, O, F: (15s6p3d1f) contracted to [9s5p3d1f] for Al, P, Si, S, Cl: (20s10p6d1f) contracted to [10s7p6d1f] for Se: (23s14p10d2f) contracted to [12s9p6d2f] for Sc, Ti, V, Cr, Mn, Fe, Co, Ni, Cu, Zn: (25s17p10d3f2g) contracted to [17s10p7d3f2g] The references for the basis sets are: T.
